spanGrp.span: it is not like we used to live.
(_) ka rö ñajiña sa sẽr-gẽ bi kuna
they were given a degree and educate children.
Je ĩã (_) juyukwö mẽnã jie-wa (_) të yabla yue-gẽ
se wã se wã nãglö mĩ-gẽ
tara ka rö tã'ĩ wã kuna
With it we can buy things,
Je je wa se se të jirö tũe-gẽ jiro
but not many, as it is said.
tara ka rö tã'ĩ (_) í she-gẽ-nã tã'ĩ wã bi kuna
many work at Pindeko planting pineapples.
muchos maleska siga-wa shkablö-gẽ rö Pindeko y piña töbiö
Jiska ka kenẽ ta mẽnẽbi shkablö-glö bi
here where we live we plant corn
jiska se sa sẽr-gẽ rö mãĩ (_) jirö ke-gẽ se të (hm) kuö bi
and things to make banana drinks and corn beverage
jirö bi je wa se të bokol chokao
Now many things have come to us,
ya jiska jeska mãĩ jirö (eh) jirö mẽnẽwãũ-ka tã'ĩ
and some people cannot believe it,
entonse moskawa ka të í ku-gẽ ĩã
but some kilometers away from here way up,
some people still live the right way.
pe sẽr-gẽ je jie-wa sẽr-gẽ ĩã rö böi
They still live and practice our language.’
je jie-wa të jele se ktö' kuge-gẽ ĩã böi
